intro: Phyllanthus omahakensis, commonly known as the Omaha kenesis plant, is a species native to specific regions in Africa. It belongs to the Euphorbiaceae family, which includes a variety of flowering plants. The plant is characterized by its small, clustered leaves and unique floral structures. It typically grows in moist, shady environments, such as forest understories. Due to its limited distribution, it is of interest to botanists and conservationists alike.
